    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-13T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-13T10:00:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/7209: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-13T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 13, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 14—1:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>598. My 574, June 11, 5 p.m. British Ambassador informed me yesterday
                        Saraçoğlu<note n="71" xml:id="d855fn71">Sükrü Saraçoğlu, Turkish Minister
                        for Foreign Affairs.</note> had expressed readiness of Turkish Government to
                    enter into negotiations for a new Anglo-Turkish chrome agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
